-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_8420380\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_8420380\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ibc1665703531301.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ibc1665703531301.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ibc1665703531301.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ibc1665703531301\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Choose the level of I/O messages that are displayed in the message frame or transcript window.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ibc1665703531301__p_d175784e1_d175785e1_d175786e1\">The place where messages are displayed is determined\n      by the settings in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Message Frame</span> tab.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ibc1665703531301__section_epv_lqh_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d162440e60\">I/O Print Fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ibc1665703531301__p_d175790e1_d175791e1_d175792e1\">The fields correspond to the following messages\n            levels:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Message Codes for Uniface I/O</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> Code </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 1 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\">Store\n\t\t\t\t sequence messages. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zll1665702716203.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zll1665702716203.html\" title=\"These messages show whether the entity is being updated or inserted (Store) or deleted (Delete), or whether the named referential integrity constraint is being applied to a many entity.\">Message Level 1: Store Sequence Messages</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 2 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> Connector requests. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ehf1665702716336.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ehf1665702716336.html\" title=\"These messages provide different types of information depending on the connector request issued.\">Message Level 2: DBMS Connector Requests</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 4 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> Return values from Fetch and Select connector requests. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yqr1665702717171.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yqr1665702717171.html\" title=\"These messages show either the number of hits selected, or the length of the I/O buffer fetched. If there is enough room, this information is included on the same line as the connector function call messages. Otherwise, it displays on another line.\">Message Level 4: Return Values from Fetch and Select Connector Requests</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 8 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> Description from Open connector request. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"byl1665702717240.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/byl1665702717240.html\" title=\"This message shows the values used by the connector when opening the file or table. This information is used primarily for debugging DBMS connectors.\">Message Level 8: Description Block from Open Connector Request</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 16 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> Descriptions from the\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">where</code>,<code class=\"ph codeph\">order</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">by</code>\n                     clauses. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oic1665702717312.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oic1665702717312.html\" title=\"These messages show which where and order by clauses are generated by Uniface.\">Message Level 16: Descriptions From where and order by Clauses</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 32 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> Generated SQL (if available). For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zxv1665702717381.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zxv1665702717381.html\" title=\"These messages show the SQL instructions generated by Uniface to execute I/O. This information is only available with SQL-based DBMSs.\">Message Level 32: Generated SQL</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 64 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> All system calls Uniface sends to operating system. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rnp1665702717449.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rnp1665702717449.html\" title=\"These messages show all the system calls, or subprocesses that Uniface starts at the operating system level, such as spools, spawns, and so on.\">Message Level 64: All System Calls Uniface Sends to Operating System</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 128 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> All calls to global objects and descriptors. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"axy1665702717519.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/axy1665702717519.html\" title=\"These messages record all calls for signatures (entity and component descriptors) and global objects.\">Message Level 128: All Calls to Global Objects and Descriptors</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 1024 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\"> Network messages </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__1\"> 2048 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ibc1665703531301__table_d18503e1_d18504e1_d18505e1__entry__2\">Image loader information </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/utv1665703530936.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Debugger Settings</a><p>Specify diagnostic settings for the current Debugger session.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yno1665703531917.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Triggers</a><p>Choose the triggers you want to be enabled or disabled for debugging, or those that you want to be set as breakpoints.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ppp1665703531653.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Tracing</a><p>Choose the level or type of ProcScript-related tracing to be displayed in the message frame or transcript window.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uha1665703532184.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Errors</a><p>Set a specific ProcScript error value ($procerror) as a breakpoint.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sev1665703532366.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Message Frame</a><p>Specify whether the clrmess ProcScript instruction is enabled or disabled, and whether application messages are sent to the application's message frame or to the application's transcript window.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqh1665702549702.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>I/O Message Levels</a><p>Most of the messages that display in the message frame are determined by the I/O message level. The I/O message is a number that is determined by adding up the codes of the applicable message types.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8420380\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8420380\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Settings: I/O Print Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Choose the level of I/O messages that are displayed in the message frame or transcript window. The place where messages are displayed is determined by the settings in the Message Frame tab. I/O Print Fields The fields correspond to the following messages levels: Table 1. Message Codes for Uniface I/O Code Description 1 Store sequence messages. For more information, see Message Level 1: Store Sequence Messages . 2 Connector requests. For more information, see Message Level 2: DBMS Connector Requests . 4 Return values from Fetch and Select connector requests. For more information, see Message Level 4: Return Values from Fetch and Select Connector Requests . 8 Description from Open connector request. For more information, see Message Level 8: Description Block from Open Connector Request . 16 Descriptions from the where , order , and by clauses. For more information, see Message Level 16: Descriptions From where and order by Clauses . 32 Generated SQL (if available). For more information, see Message Level 32: Generated SQL . 64 All system calls Uniface sends to operating system. For more information, see Message Level 64: All System Calls Uniface Sends to Operating System . 128 All calls to global objects and descriptors. For more information, see Message Level 128: All Calls to Global Objects and Descriptors . 1024 Network messages 2048 Image loader information Related Links Debugger Settings Specify diagnostic settings for the current Debugger session. Settings: Triggers Choose the triggers you want to be enabled or disabled for debugging, or those that you want to be set as breakpoints. Settings: Tracing Choose the level or type of ProcScript-related tracing to be displayed in the message frame or transcript window. Settings: Errors Set a specific ProcScript error value ($procerror) as a breakpoint. Settings: Message Frame Specify whether the clrmess ProcScript instruction is enabled or disabled, and whether application messages are sent to the application's message frame or to the application's transcript window. I/O Message Levels Most of the messages that display in the message frame are determined by the I/O message level. The I/O message is a number that is determined by adding up the codes of the applicable message types. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}